.TH "lpfc_scsi_prep_dma_buf_s3" 9 "lpfc_scsi_prep_dma_buf_s3" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_scsi_prep_dma_buf_s3 \- DMA mapping for scsi buffer to SLI3 IF spec
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_scsi_prep_dma_buf_s3
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "struct lpfc_io_buf *lpfc_cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
The Hba for which this call is being executed.
.IP "lpfc_cmd" 12
The scsi buffer which is going to be mapped.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine does the pci dma mapping for scatter-gather list of scsi cmnd
field of \fIlpfc_cmd\fP for device with SLI-3 interface spec. This routine scans
through sg elements and format the bde. This routine also initializes all
IOCB fields which are dependent on scsi command request buffer.

Return codes:
1 - Error
0 - Success
